                            <comment id="12694027" author="noble.paul" created="Tue, 31 Mar 2009 10:14:44 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;read_timeout is set to 10 secs and conn_timeout is set to 5 secs&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12698342" author="shalinmangar" created="Mon, 13 Apr 2009 09:37:23 +0100"  >&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Introduces httpConnTimeout and httpReadTimeout configuration parameters&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;HttpClient is created per core only if timeout is specified. Otherwise the core uses the static shared instance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I plan to commit shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12698345" author="shalinmangar" created="Mon, 13 Apr 2009 09:42:31 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 764371.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12699546" author="shalinmangar" created="Thu, 16 Apr 2009 07:28:59 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Changes default connection timeout to 5 seconds and read timeout to 20 seconds.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Keeping a large read timeout will avoid people tripping over this when downloading 1MB chunks with a single read operation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll commit shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
